FeatureName: Spray Can Tool

Description:
    The spray can tool simulates aerosol-style painting by scattering many small
    dots of the current color within a circular radius around the cursor. As the
    user drags the mouse, the tool continuously generates randomized points,
    creating a soft, diffused spray-paint effect similar to digital art software.
    The density, size, and distribution of spray particles reflect the current
    stroke width setting, allowing for fine misting or heavier spray patterns.
    All dots created during a spray action are stored as a single SprayCan shape
    to support consistent undo/redo and efficient rendering.

Reference:
    US4.005
