FeatureName: AI Random Shape Generator

Description:
	Implements an AI feature that randomly generates shapes with varying types,
	colors, sizes, and fill styles for automatic creative compositions.
	The seed feature allows the user to keep a record of the previous randomly
	generated shape based on the number entered and when the number is re-entered
	those same shapes are generated at the same position in the same size
	with the users chosen colours, outlines, etc.

Reference:
	US4.006
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
FeatureName: Random Scenery Generator

Description:
    The scenery feature allows users to instantly generate a prebuilt, themed
    background on the canvas. A library of hardcoded sceneries—such as beaches,
    cities, gardens, etc is stored in the SceneryLibrary. When the user selects a
    scenery option, the system loads the corresponding list of Shapes and adds
    them to the model using a BatchAddCommand. This means the entire scenery counts
    as one undoable action, and all shapes are drawn in the correct order to form
    a cohesive scene. The feature provides an easy starting point for creative
    drawing, allowing users to sketch on top of a complete background without
    constructing it manually.

Reference:
    US4.007
